Speaking at an event in Sandton, Johannesburg, Huawei South Africa General Manager Likhun Zhao launched the Huawei Mate RS Porsche Design in South Africa. The smartphone was unveiled at the company’s P20 Series launch event in Paris, France earlier this year. Huawei said the 256GB model of the device will be available locally, and that local stock of the smartphone is limited compared to more mainstream devices. The Mate RS Porsche Design will be available for purchase exclusively through MTN for R26,459 – available from 9 May 2018. The specifications of the luxury device, along with photos of it, are posted below.